Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Bowen.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Bowen (1989), 46 Ohio St. 3d 603.]

(No. D.D. 87-35 — Submitted October 11, 1989 — Decided October 25, 1989.)

The application for reinstatement to the practice of law is granted. John W. E. Bowen is reinstated to the practice of law in the state of Ohio.

(For earlier case, see [1988], 38 Ohio St. 3d 323, 528 N.E. 2d 172.)

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur,
